ow CNN calculates the output size using:

Input Image Size
Kernel (Filter) Size
Stride
Given in Image
Input Image Size
7 × 7
Filter (Kernel) Size
3 × 3
Stride
Stride = 1
What Happens?

The 3×3 filter moves over the 7×7 image.

Since:

Stride = 1

The filter moves:

1 step right
then next row
again 1 step
Why Output Becomes 5×5?

Because the filter cannot go outside the image.

CNN calculates how many positions the filter can fit.

Formula

Output Size=

(N−F) / S + 1
	​
Where:

N = Input size
F = Filter size
S = Stride

Apply Values

========

Apply Values

= (7 - 3) / 1 + 1

= 4 / 1 + 1

= 4 + 1

= 5

